6
00:00:12,620 --> 00:00:15,740
[7HD Channel]

7
00:00:15,740 --> 00:00:18,700
[IQIYI]

8
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:26,140
♫ I’m just someone, who isn’t that perfect ♫

9
00:00:26,140 --> 00:00:32,500
♫ But for you, I’m willing to give it all ♫

10
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:36,740
♫ Whether you’d love me, or care about me or not ♫

11
00:00:36,740 --> 00:00:42,260
♫ That’s for you to decide, but as for me I’m… ♫

12
00:00:42,260 --> 00:00:44,780
♫ (Will be right here) not going anywhere ♫

13
00:00:44,780 --> 00:00:47,380
♫ (Hold my hand) stay by my side ♫

14
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:52,300
♫ Just turn around and you’ll see ♫

15
00:00:52,660 --> 00:00:56,300
♫ You’ll always have me by your side ♫

16
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,860
♫ In this marriage that our love will last forever♫

17
00:00:58,860 --> 00:01:04,300
♫ I promise I’ll give you all my heart♫

18
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:07,140
♫ Remember when I said…♫

19
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:12,220
♫ That I’ll take great care of you♫

20
00:01:12,220 --> 00:01:20,740
♫ I promise those words will always stay true♫

21
00:01:20,740 --> 00:01:23,260
[The Earth]

22
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:24,580
[Previously]
[Din]: Rose.

23
00:01:24,580 --> 00:01:25,260
Yes?

24
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:26,700
Please marry me.

25
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,730
[Lom]: I’m the one who suggested that to her.

26
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:33,900
This marriage will help keep you safe from Mr. Wasupol.

27
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:35,900
I will marry you.

28
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:40,700
[Din]: We also have to make it legal and sign a marriage certificate.

29
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:46,220
[Rose]: I understand that we should make it look real both by law and in practice.

30
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,460
[Nam]: We’ll help take care of the wedding arrangement.

31
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:51,060
Thank you so much.

32
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:53,340
For the security part, just leave it to me.

33
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:57,700
And for the prewedding photoshoot, Fai will take care of it.

34
00:01:58,930 --> 00:01:59,729
Fine.

35
00:02:00,330 --> 00:02:01,980
But only because Nam asked me so.

36
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:08,500
Din, have I done anything to upset Fai?

37
00:02:09,539 --> 00:02:15,300
Fai mightn’t look so friendly but if you get to know her more, she’s actually a nice person.

38
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:29,740
Sis, let’s do the prewedding photoshoot tomorrow. But it might look a bit dry in the background though.

39
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,780
Then, should we do it at your farm instead? It’d look prettier there.

40
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:45,500
Good idea. Can we do that, Rose?

41
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,100
Sure.

42
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:55,800
Miss Din, Miss Din! Mr. Wasupol is here to see you.

43
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,660
Is Wasu with him too?

44
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:03,060
No, Miss. Just Mr. Wasupol and two of his men. They’re waiting in their car now.

45
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:07,140
How dare he show his face here.  Come, Sis. I’ll go with you.

46
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:09,500
I’ll go too. Wanna see his shameless face.

47
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:15,780
No need. All of you just stay here. Please take care of Rose for me. I’ll go talk to him.

48
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:33,200
I’m here to talk to you. Why did you force Rose to move in with you?

49
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:38,060
You must have misunderstood something. Rose is willing to stay here

50
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:45,100
What about your wedding with Rose? You’re taking advantage of her while Thipakorn is still in a coma.

51
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:53,420
You’re well aware that my family and hers have long agreed that Rose should marry Wasu.

52
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:56,180
No matter what, Rose has to marry Wasu.

53
00:03:56,180 --> 00:04:00,580
If only you’d taken pride in whatever you still have left of your family name, you wouldn’t have done this.

54
00:04:00,580 --> 00:04:02,980
It’s just your words, with no written agreement.

55
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:08,780
I can also claim that before the accident, Uncle Thip told me to marry Rose.

56
00:04:08,780 --> 00:04:11,860
Don’t you think you’re going a bit too far?

57
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:18,019
Think about it, what if I tell everyone about this?

58
00:04:18,019 --> 00:04:20,420
People might be talking that your parents haven't raised you well enough.

59
00:04:21,339 --> 00:04:22,700
That you have no shame.

60
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:25,740
Neither have I then.

61
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:30,860
Rose.

62
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:33,800
Because I chose to marry her at my own will.

63
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:45,460
I apologize for interrupting. But I have to protect the woman I want to marry.

64
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:53,820
I don’t love Wasu, so I can’t keep my parents’ promise to marry him.

65
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:57,300
And above all that, Uncle…

66
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,380
I love her.

67
00:05:08,730 --> 00:05:12,930
She’s the person I love and want to marry.

68
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:23,860
You only came back not long ago, how on earth could you love her?

69
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,730
You still don’t know her well.

70
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,540
And she’s also a girl like you.

71
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:35,600
We’ve known each other since we were little.

72
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:39,820
There might be times when we lost touch while I was still in the US.

73
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:48,820
But my father has always kept me posted about her.
So, when we met again, we could feel the sparks pretty quickly.

74
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:54,860
She is warm, kind, and very sweet.

75
00:05:56,700 --> 00:06:01,060
The next thing I knew, I’ve already fallen head over heels for her.

76
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:08,220
Uncle, can you please not come between our love?

77
00:06:11,260 --> 00:06:15,760
If you’re free, I'd like to invite you to our wedding too.

78
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,100
Are you all right, Din?

79
00:06:51,530 --> 00:06:54,100
Yes, I’m okay.

80
00:06:55,730 --> 00:06:58,900
She’s probably still shocked after hearing you confessing your love to her.

81
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:02,060
Well...

82
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:10,460
I only said that to make Mr. Wasupol believe Din and I are in love. Please don’t take it seriously.

83
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:14,660
Thank you, Rose, for standing up for me.

84
00:07:15,860 --> 00:07:19,200
You did a great job there, Rose. Got him quite dumbfounded.

85
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:26,130
But coming here to speak to you himself, I don’t think he would let it slide so easily.

86
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,700
I’m not going to let anyone hurt you.

87
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:35,330
Please promise me that you’ll be more careful from now on.

88
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,740
Yes, I promise.

89
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,060
Someone is getting flustered.

90
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:52,260
Fine, I approve.

91
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:02,860
I approve of your marriage with Rose. And I also accept her as one of our family…

92
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:06,380
and will no longer be against her too.

93
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:10,100
Thanks a lot for understanding me, Fai.

94
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:18,260
I really don’t trust that smile.

95
00:08:19,130 --> 00:08:21,380
Like we could ever trust this rascal.

96
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:34,059
What are you doing, Boss?

97
00:08:35,220 --> 00:08:38,340
Yes? Did you just call me?

98
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,940
It’s only you and me here, Boss.

99
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:44,860
B…Boss?

100
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:47,860
Yes. Boss.

101
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:55,580
Why are you calling me Boss? I’m younger than you.

102
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:59,940
I don’t care if you’re younger or older. As long as you’re cool, I’ll call you Boss.

103
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,380
Are you bothering her since early morning?

104
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:07,260
Of course, not. I was just saying hi to Boss Rose.

105
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:11,460
Please don’t mind her. She’s quite nuts.

106
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,900
Geez, first thing in the morning.

107
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,300
Where’s Din?

108
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:20,330
She’s left since dawn to drop Nam off. She should be back soon.

109
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:22,980
Oh, Nam has gone home?

110
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,820
Yes, urgent work came up.

111
00:09:26,460 --> 00:09:29,600
That one is busier than a superstar.

112
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,540
Are you guys having breakfast?

113
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:37,060
You’re back? Took you long enough.

114
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,300
Can I eat now?

115
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:40,740
Go ahead.

116
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:47,600
All right then, let’s hurry and finish your breakfast so we can start shooting for the prewedding before the sun gets too strong.

117
00:09:49,660 --> 00:09:51,300
Have you got your outfits ready, Boss?

118
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:55,600
Yes, I have them all ready.

119
00:09:56,460 --> 00:09:58,300
What? Boss?

120
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:28,780
Okay, like this. Whose sister is this? So good-looking.

121
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,780
Okay, ready?

122
00:10:34,660 --> 00:10:39,560
Can you two move a little closer to her? We don’t need social distancing now.

123
00:10:41,130 --> 00:10:41,930
Like this?

124
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:46,580
Seriously, that little? Closer please.

125
00:10:51,580 --> 00:10:55,700
Wow, so close I’d need a microscope to see it. Lom!

126
00:10:59,580 --> 00:11:02,940
Put your arm around her waist. Don’t just stand there like a log.

127
00:11:03,620 --> 00:11:05,180
Give her some respect.

128
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:14,540
It’s all right. I don’t mind at all. So that our photos will look pretty.

129
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,980
Hug me a little tighter.

130
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:28,660
Smile, sis. Or else they’d think you’re not married for real.

131
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,960
Can you stop bossing me around?

132
00:11:31,330 --> 00:11:32,860
Smile!

133
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,360
Please smile.

134
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:39,420
Or else people mightn’t believe we’re married for real.

135
00:11:44,740 --> 00:11:45,700
Smile like this.

136
00:11:56,260 --> 00:11:59,980
Smile like someone who’s in love. Like this.

137
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:19,460
Hello, sir. This way, please.

138
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:25,060
We’ve prepared a seat for you. Please let us know if you need anything.

139
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,460
Over here, please.

140
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,160
Food and drinks are available over there.

141
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:31,900
Yes.

142
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:35,540
In case you’d like to have your meal here, please feel free.

143
00:13:35,860 --> 00:13:36,660
Yes.

144
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:51,730
I already told our men to keep watch at the entrance.
Some of us are also disguised as guests.

145
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:53,820
Good. If there’s anything, tell me immediately.

146
00:13:53,820 --> 00:13:54,700
Yes, sir.

147
00:14:14,330 --> 00:14:16,300
Excuse me, can I take your picture, please?

148
00:14:25,730 --> 00:14:28,420
Give these two glasses of wine to the governor and his wife.

149
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:30,460
Also ask them if they need anything.

150
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:50,340
It’s so lovely.

151
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,180
Do you like it?

152
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:53,780
Yes.

153
00:14:55,260 --> 00:15:00,780
Without Nam, Lom, and Fai; it wouldn’t have happened at all.

154
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:03,420
I don’t think I can manage all this alone.

155
00:15:04,730 --> 00:15:07,300
I should go and thank everyone after this.

156
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:10,100
They are willing to do it for us.

157
00:15:11,130 --> 00:15:12,530
But I still feel bad.

158
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:19,100
I already told you that we’re a family now.

159
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:20,940
Yes?

160
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:28,740
From now on, Amornjinda will never have to walk alone. They’ll always have Watinwanich by their side.

161
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:33,060
Thank you so much.

162
00:15:34,460 --> 00:15:42,220
Even though this is just a fake marriage, I do feel safe with you here.

163
00:15:57,530 --> 00:16:01,380
Miss Din, Miss Rose, Mr. Wasu is causing a ruckus at the entrance.

164
00:16:07,460 --> 00:16:08,600
I said you can’t go in.

165
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,530
Why the hell can’t I?

166
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:12,360
You’re not invited.

167
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:14,780
Did that bastard tell you so?

168
00:16:16,130 --> 00:16:16,930
What are you doing here?

169
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:21,500
Loser, did you tell your men to take care of your guests like this?

170
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,820
Wasu, please don’t cause any problem here.

171
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:27,580
That’s not why I’m here, Rose.

172
00:16:27,930 --> 00:16:30,540
I’m here on behalf of my father.

173
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:33,140
Didn't you invite him yourself?

174
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,400
Fine, go in.

175
00:16:53,330 --> 00:16:54,160
Let's go.

176
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:11,940
1 2 3! That’s it. Thank you.

177
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:24,859
Rose, come and take a picture with me.

178
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:36,180
Hey, mug face. Take us a picture.

179
00:17:36,730 --> 00:17:38,180
Son of a bitch.

180
00:17:38,180 --> 00:17:39,020
Fai!

181
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,820
Just you wait.

182
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:49,000
Give me your best smile.

183
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,780
Done. Off you go.

184
00:17:59,330 --> 00:18:01,260
You look so beautiful today.

185
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:06,940
Rose, can you please go talk to the governor for me? I saw him looking our way.

186
00:18:07,730 --> 00:18:08,500
Sure.

187
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:17,160
Do you really think having the governor here could save your fucking ass from me?

188
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:20,980
You can try it if you want.

189
00:18:21,660 --> 00:18:25,380
But there’s one thing I’m sure of--you’ll definitely lose more than you’d gain.

190
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:32,340
I don’t care. I’ll do anything to make Rose mine.

191
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:37,140
She’s not yours. And she has never been one.

192
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:44,820
Mark my words, from now on, Rose is my wife. Don’t you ever forget that.

193
00:18:44,820 --> 00:18:45,740
- You!
- Mr. Wasu.

194
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:46,900
Remember what your father said.

195
00:18:52,730 --> 00:18:54,860
You’ll never die in peace, Bastard!

196
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:19,400
It’s time to exchange rings, Sis.

197
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:44,620
Din, this is not the ring I’ve chosen.

198
00:20:45,930 --> 00:20:48,140
I told Nam to get a new one for you.

199
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:53,660
You're the most valuable thing in my life.

200
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:57,940
That’s why I want you to have the best of everything.

201
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:29,100
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

202
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:33,980
What to do now? Everyone’s looking at us.

203
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:40,060
Just ignore them.

204
00:22:42,620 --> 00:22:45,530
But other guests might not believe it then.

205
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:51,380
What should we do then?

206
00:22:53,060 --> 00:22:55,860
How about a cheek-to-cheek kiss?

207
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:00,500
Okay.

208
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:29,220
Rose.

209
00:23:29,220 --> 00:23:29,940
Yes?

210
00:23:29,940 --> 00:23:32,980
I…I…

211
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,500
Din!

212
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:35,260
Din!

213
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:36,940
Miss Din fainted! She fainted!

214
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:37,780
Miss Din!

215
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,260
Sis!

216
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:42,660
Miss Din fainted!

217
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,460
Please don’t die, Sis!

218
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:49,380
Miss Din!

219
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:51,140
- Sis!
- Miss Din!

220
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:52,140
Sis!

221
00:23:52,820 --> 00:23:54,300
Miss Din!

222
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,260
My dear sis.

223
00:23:55,260 --> 00:23:56,340
Are you really having it that bad?

224
00:24:55,620 --> 00:25:00,180
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

225
00:25:21,260 --> 00:25:25,000
May I…come in?

226
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:29,020
Of course. It’s your room.

227
00:25:38,700 --> 00:25:39,960
Are you feeling better?

228
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,100
Yes.

229
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:53,900
I see you haven’t showered yet. Aren’t you feeling a bit sticky right now?

230
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:59,420
I just got up. I’m about to go shower.

231
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:36,100
Why are you packing?

232
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:39,000
I’m going to sleep with Fai in the guest bedroom.

233
00:26:39,130 --> 00:26:40,730
So that you can rest freely here.

234
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:46,940
Please don’t. I can go sleep in my room.

235
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:49,540
This way, you won’t have to bother Fai too.

236
00:26:49,620 --> 00:26:53,980
No, you can’t. If Aunt Chan and Moddang find out,

237
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:56,780
they might think it suspicious why newlyweds like us are sleeping in separate rooms.

238
00:26:57,500 --> 00:26:58,300
You’re right.

239
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:08,380
Just sleep here. I’ll sneak out and make sure no one sees me.

240
00:27:09,580 --> 00:27:10,540
Okay.

241
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:12,620
I’m going then.

242
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:20,260
Miss Din! What are you doing? Isn’t it already past the time for the bridal bed ceremony?

243
00:28:27,100 --> 00:28:32,060
I just want to make sure everything in the guest room is all right, in case Fai might need anything.

244
00:28:33,100 --> 00:28:35,380
Oh, that’s nothing at all. You can leave it to me.

245
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:38,380
Please go back into your room, Miss.

246
00:28:38,380 --> 00:28:43,140
Don’t you know it’s a jinx to leave your room on your wedding night?

247
00:28:43,140 --> 00:28:48,700
You shouldn’t come out until the next morning. Okay?

248
00:28:49,660 --> 00:28:51,100
N…next morning?

249
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:52,800
Yes.

250
00:28:56,100 --> 00:29:00,020
I’ll leave it to you then.

251
00:29:00,060 --> 00:29:02,380
Don’t worry. Let me take care of it.

252
00:29:02,380 --> 00:29:08,020
Please go back inside, my dear miss. And don’t come out no matter what. Don’t open the door even if you hear anything.

253
00:29:08,340 --> 00:29:13,340
Stay inside with your wife until the next morning. Our ancestors are really serious about this, Miss.

254
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:15,400
Good night.

255
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,530
I guess you're stuck with me tonight.

256
00:29:43,260 --> 00:29:45,460
We’d better go shower. It’s late.

257
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:50,460
You mean together?

258
00:29:51,860 --> 00:29:55,960
I mean after you’re done showering, I’ll shower too.

259
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:03,160
Or…do you want to get in the bath together?

260
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:07,600
N…No.

261
00:30:12,530 --> 00:30:13,780
Make it quick.

262
00:30:33,460 --> 00:30:34,380
Din.

263
00:30:35,100 --> 00:30:36,660
What are you doing?

264
00:30:37,220 --> 00:30:40,900
Oh, just praying before going to bed.

265
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:44,400
I mean why are you sleeping on the floor?

266
00:30:46,060 --> 00:30:47,600
I’ll sleep here tonight.

267
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,930
You can take the bed. It’s comfier.

268
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:51,700
You can’t do that!

269
00:30:52,660 --> 00:30:55,700
I already feel guilty enough for taking up space in your room like this.

270
00:30:55,700 --> 00:30:57,340
Let’s sleep together.

271
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:00,260
Sleep together?

272
00:31:00,660 --> 00:31:04,700
I don’t think it’s appropriate.

273
00:31:04,900 --> 00:31:06,700
But if you’re going to sleep on the floor,

274
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:09,260
I don’t think it’s appropriate either.

275
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:12,260
Why not?

276
00:31:13,900 --> 00:31:14,900
First,

277
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:16,900
this is your room.

278
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:18,620
Second,

279
00:31:19,220 --> 00:31:21,300
you must be exhausted after a long day.

280
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:22,860
Third,

281
00:31:22,860 --> 00:31:27,020
you’re older than me. I can’t sleep on a higher ground than you.

282
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,060
Oh.

283
00:31:36,500 --> 00:31:37,760
But I’m comfortable like this.

284
00:31:37,930 --> 00:31:38,730
But I’m not!

285
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:39,780
I can sleep here!

286
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:40,420
No, you can’t!

287
00:31:40,420 --> 00:31:42,180
Yes, I can!

288
00:31:42,180 --> 00:31:43,460
No, you can’t! Oh!

289
00:32:07,060 --> 00:32:09,220
If it really makes you feel awkward,

290
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:17,380
should we just…stay up all night then?

291
00:32:19,460 --> 00:32:21,340
How about we…

292
00:32:22,380 --> 00:32:25,900
stay up all night to tighten our relationship?

293
00:32:31,100 --> 00:32:34,860
Tighten our relationship…all night?

294
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:38,500
How?

295
00:32:57,360 --> 00:33:00,660
So…

296
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:04,860
What should we talk about?

297
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:15,330
How about your life when you studied in the US?

298
00:33:20,100 --> 00:33:23,160
I’m more interested in how you began to look after Saen Rak farm.

299
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:32,800
I’m all ears.

300
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:38,900
W…well…

301
00:33:38,900 --> 00:33:42,020
At first,

302
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:48,580
looking after the whole farm was really hard for me.

303
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,580
But right now, even though it’s still tough,

304
00:33:52,100 --> 00:33:53,740
I’m really happy.

305
00:33:53,740 --> 00:33:58,500
That I’m able to carry on with what my father had done and even make it better.

306
00:34:02,300 --> 00:34:05,100
And that’s my story. Now, it’s your…

307
00:35:11,660 --> 00:35:14,700
Good night, Rose.

308
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:24,980
Aunt Chan, is Rose up yet?

309
00:38:26,100 --> 00:38:27,300
Yes.

310
00:38:29,820 --> 00:38:30,860
Rose.

311
00:38:31,500 --> 00:38:32,580
You’re up?

312
00:38:34,540 --> 00:38:37,500
You do all the cooking yourself today?

313
00:38:39,530 --> 00:38:41,960
Isn’t it usually Aunt Chan’s job?

314
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:48,100
I just…want to do something special for our first morning after the marriage.

315
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:54,700
Whoever gets to be your wife is absolutely lucky.

316
00:38:55,100 --> 00:38:57,620
You take such amazing care of her.

317
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:08,020
Actually, I planned to serve you breakfast in bed.

318
00:39:08,020 --> 00:39:11,260
But you got up first.

319
00:39:11,540 --> 00:39:12,660
Then,

320
00:39:13,260 --> 00:39:15,900
maybe I should go back to sleep.

321
00:39:15,900 --> 00:39:18,300
So that you can serve me breakfast in bed!

322
00:39:18,530 --> 00:39:19,380
Are you serious?

323
00:39:21,300 --> 00:39:22,460
Just kidding.

324
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:31,000
Why don’t you go shower first then?

325
00:39:32,130 --> 00:39:37,420
Give me 20 minutes. I’ll dress up nicely and have breakfast with you.

326
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:39,400
Okay.

327
00:39:58,460 --> 00:40:01,020
Wow! Looks yummy!

328
00:40:01,530 --> 00:40:03,580
Did you get up early to make all this?

329
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:04,760
Hey, don’t!

330
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:07,060
It’s for Rose.

331
00:40:07,600 --> 00:40:10,180
Go tell Aunt Chan if you want to eat anything.

332
00:40:10,460 --> 00:40:12,700
I see. They’re for Rose.

333
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:16,460
-  It’s a lot. She won’t be able to finish them.
-  Hey, I said no!

334
00:40:16,460 --> 00:40:18,500
- What if it’s not enough?
- So hungry!

335
00:40:18,500 --> 00:40:20,140
Hey! Don’t!

336
00:40:20,900 --> 00:40:24,060
These are all for Rose. Don’t touch them.

337
00:40:25,820 --> 00:40:26,700
Fai.

338
00:40:26,700 --> 00:40:27,460
Hm?

339
00:40:28,300 --> 00:40:31,130
I think our sister is getting confused about what's real and what's not.

340
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:33,980
Look, she even got up so early to cook for the bride.

341
00:40:34,300 --> 00:40:36,620
Aren’t you getting too carried away?

342
00:40:36,660 --> 00:40:41,060
Now, I’m starting to doubt if this is a fake marriage or not.

343
00:40:42,820 --> 00:40:43,340
Right?

344
00:40:43,340 --> 00:40:44,500
Hey!

345
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:45,380
Don’t!

346
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:57,060
I told you, didn’t I?

347
00:40:57,760 --> 00:41:00,300
That you shouldn’t go cause a ruckus at their wedding.

348
00:41:03,330 --> 00:41:05,730
I just went there to congratulate them.

349
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:12,200
You think I don’t know you well enough?

350
00:41:12,730 --> 00:41:14,160
You just don’t want to lose to Din.

351
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:20,180
That bastard stole Rose from me, Dad!

352
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:22,400
I don’t believe one bit that Rose loves her.

353
00:41:22,900 --> 00:41:24,860
There’s no way they’re married for real.

354
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:30,980
If that’s what you believe,

355
00:41:32,100 --> 00:41:33,660
I’ll prove it to you.

356
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:37,140
What are you going to do?

357
00:41:48,220 --> 00:41:50,700
Are they fresh?

358
00:41:54,660 --> 00:41:55,600
Mr. Boat.

359
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:56,660
Mr. Wasupol.

360
00:41:56,730 --> 00:41:57,600
I’d like you to try this.

361
00:41:58,600 --> 00:42:02,260
It’s our latest one. Please try,  you can order from us next time if you like it.

362
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:03,860
Thank you.

363
00:42:12,930 --> 00:42:13,730
Here you go.

364
00:42:13,730 --> 00:42:14,530
Yes?

365
00:42:15,060 --> 00:42:16,900
Don’t worry. I already gave you a discount.

366
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:18,860
Thank you so much.

367
00:42:22,260 --> 00:42:23,220
How is Wasu?

368
00:42:23,220 --> 00:42:24,620
Has he eaten anything yet?

369
00:42:24,860 --> 00:42:26,620
He’s still not better, sir.

370
00:42:28,930 --> 00:42:30,300
Is Mr. Wasu all right?

371
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:32,400
I actually wanted to ask you earlier.

372
00:42:32,760 --> 00:42:34,660
Usually, Mr. Wasu would take care of this job himself.

373
00:42:35,060 --> 00:42:37,000
But today, you’re here instead.

374
00:42:37,560 --> 00:42:41,220
Mr. Wasu is heartbroken because Miss Din snatched Miss Rose from him and married her.

375
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:43,500
He hasn’t been able to eat or sleep for many days now.

376
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:45,300
Snatched?

377
00:42:46,130 --> 00:42:47,560
What happened, Mr. Wasupol?

378
00:42:56,420 --> 00:43:00,380
Actually, the parents from our farm and Chomchan farm…

379
00:43:00,820 --> 00:43:03,420
have long agreed on the engagement between Rose and Wasu.

380
00:43:05,130 --> 00:43:07,730
Wasu has loved his Rose since very little.

381
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:12,300
So, he’s now devastated and still can’t get over it.

382
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:17,860
Why would Miss Din do that?

383
00:43:18,160 --> 00:43:18,960
Yeah, why?

384
00:43:19,460 --> 00:43:25,260
I don’t know too. But I’m afraid there might be another reason behind this marriage.

385
00:43:27,100 --> 00:43:30,060
A reason behind this? What reason?

386
00:43:36,900 --> 00:43:38,540
Bee! Bee!

387
00:43:39,180 --> 00:43:44,300
Do you know that Miss Din married Miss Rose because she actually wanted to take over Chomchan farm and claimed it hers?

388
00:43:44,330 --> 00:43:44,780
What?

389
00:43:45,420 --> 00:43:49,300
I knew it! That’s why they got married out of the blue like that.

390
00:43:49,300 --> 00:43:52,780
But Miss Rose just came back not long ago. When did they fall in love?

391
00:43:53,700 --> 00:43:55,760
I heard they’ve liked each other since young.

392
00:43:56,660 --> 00:43:58,260
That’s not all, Bee.

393
00:43:58,530 --> 00:43:59,330
What else?

394
00:43:59,500 --> 00:44:02,060
You’d better zip it up and don’t tell anyone.

395
00:44:02,820 --> 00:44:06,500
Listen, Mr. Wasupol and Miss Rose’s parents…

396
00:44:06,500 --> 00:44:09,980
have long agreed to have Miss Rose engaged to Mr. Wasu.

397
00:44:09,980 --> 00:44:15,180
What? This means Miss Din stole Miss Rose from him then.

398
00:44:15,740 --> 00:44:17,180
She’s so shameless.

399
00:44:17,530 --> 00:44:21,660
Everyone in the market knows that Miss Din and Miss Rose are not married for real.

400
00:44:21,660 --> 00:44:25,060
It’s purely a marriage of convenience.

401
00:44:25,060 --> 00:44:25,700
Seller.

402
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:26,600
Yes?

403
00:44:47,130 --> 00:44:49,340
Have a safe trip. Thanks a lot.

404
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:51,020
My pleasure.

405
00:44:51,300 --> 00:44:54,060
Please take Boss Rose to visit me in Surat sometimes.

406
00:44:56,160 --> 00:44:58,140
I’ll call you later about the case.

407
00:44:58,140 --> 00:45:00,300
Okay. Thanks a lot for coming.

408
00:45:01,900 --> 00:45:03,380
Take care of yourself.

409
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:06,400
Bye Bye!

410
00:45:06,620 --> 00:45:07,460
- Let’s go.
- [Fai]: Bye Bye.

411
00:45:07,460 --> 00:45:09,580
- See you.
- [Rose]: Bye Bye! See you.

412
00:45:09,930 --> 00:45:10,730
Let’s go, Fai.

413
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:11,800
Let's go.

414
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:13,530
See you again.

415
00:45:13,530 --> 00:45:14,200
Have a safe trip.

416
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:15,000
See you.

417
00:45:33,530 --> 00:45:36,160
Miss Din, Miss Rose! We’ve got problems!

418
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:43,860
Miss Din, Miss Rose. We’ve got problems!

419
00:45:43,860 --> 00:45:44,730
What is it?

420
00:45:44,800 --> 00:45:47,660
People in the market are talking about your marriage.

421
00:45:48,960 --> 00:45:49,960
What are they saying?

422
00:45:50,300 --> 00:45:53,560
They’re saying that you two got married for mutual benefits.

423
00:45:54,100 --> 00:45:57,130
Some even say Miss Din is planning to take over Chomchan farm.

424
00:45:58,300 --> 00:46:01,460
You two are so madly in love, how could that be possible?

425
00:46:02,100 --> 00:46:05,000
What else did they say? Tell me everything.

426
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:10,130
There’s no doubt who started this rumour.

427
00:46:10,600 --> 00:46:12,560
He obviously wants to ruin your reputation.

428
00:46:13,060 --> 00:46:15,530
Wasu must really hate me for taking you away from him.

429
00:46:19,300 --> 00:46:21,500
If they can spread the rumour,

430
00:46:22,260 --> 00:46:24,600
we can find a way to stop it too.

431
00:46:27,060 --> 00:46:29,100
What are you going to do?

432
00:46:43,460 --> 00:46:46,960
Hey. So, are Miss Din and Miss Rose actually lovers?

433
00:46:47,620 --> 00:46:51,220
I don’t know too. But I also find it suspicious.

434
00:46:51,220 --> 00:46:54,860
They suddenly got married without any sign or warning.

435
00:46:56,060 --> 00:47:00,180
Nonsense. Miss Din has always taken care of Miss Rose.

436
00:47:00,820 --> 00:47:05,420
When Miss Rose first came back from the US, Miss Din even sent some of our men to keep watch over her.

437
00:47:06,900 --> 00:47:08,860
Do you know anything about it, Kaew?

438
00:47:11,160 --> 00:47:15,340
No idea too. It’s probably just a rumour after all.

439
00:47:15,500 --> 00:47:17,740
Look at that. There she is.

440
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:22,140
Din!

441
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:23,800
Rose.

442
00:47:30,730 --> 00:47:32,400
What are you doing here, Rose?

443
00:47:34,200 --> 00:47:36,260
They are watching us.

444
00:47:38,760 --> 00:47:40,700
I made you some snacks.

445
00:47:42,200 --> 00:47:43,060
Are you tired?

446
00:47:43,930 --> 00:47:44,760
Not at all.

447
00:47:46,060 --> 00:47:46,860
Thank you.

448
00:47:47,360 --> 00:47:48,460
Let me wipe off your sweat.

449
00:47:55,860 --> 00:48:00,460
They look pretty much in love to me. Seeing is believing indeed.

450
00:48:00,800 --> 00:48:03,740
Yeah, people just like to gossip.

451
00:48:08,220 --> 00:48:09,420
Thank you.

452
00:48:12,300 --> 00:48:14,000
Do you want to eat them now?

453
00:48:15,660 --> 00:48:17,460
Maybe later.

454
00:48:27,260 --> 00:48:30,020
Let me know if you want to eat anything.

455
00:48:30,600 --> 00:48:33,330
Hmm…what should I eat?

456
00:48:33,960 --> 00:48:34,900
Guava maybe?

457
00:48:35,300 --> 00:48:36,100
Guava?

458
00:48:36,130 --> 00:48:37,100
Wait.

459
00:48:37,380 --> 00:48:37,700
Yes?

460
00:48:37,700 --> 00:48:38,500
Just a second.

461
00:48:41,600 --> 00:48:42,860
Let me fix your hair a bit.

462
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:50,420
Have you finished your juice? You can have mine.

463
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:02,220
I guess the rumour wasn't true then.

464
00:49:02,730 --> 00:49:04,560
They look so madly in love.

465
00:49:05,460 --> 00:49:07,900
I heard they went to sign a marriage certificate this morning.

466
00:49:08,360 --> 00:49:11,700
That’s why. Look how Miss Din is looking at her.

467
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:15,140
Even my hubby has never looked at me that way.

468
00:49:16,020 --> 00:49:17,820
So, it’s not true then.

469
00:49:18,220 --> 00:49:20,020
- They're clearly in love.
- Yeah.

470
00:49:20,020 --> 00:49:22,380
Who on earth said she plans to take over Chomchan farm?

471
00:49:25,180 --> 00:49:26,660
Oh, the coconut juice again.

472
00:49:26,660 --> 00:49:27,700
Can I have one more?

473
00:49:27,700 --> 00:49:28,860
Sure, from this shop?

474
00:49:28,860 --> 00:49:30,620
Yes, oh!

475
00:49:31,180 --> 00:49:32,260
Rose!

476
00:49:37,730 --> 00:49:38,780
Does it hurt?

477
00:49:40,900 --> 00:49:43,540
Yes, my wrist too.

478
00:49:43,800 --> 00:49:44,900
Can you stand up?

479
00:49:47,580 --> 00:49:50,180
1 2 3.

480
00:49:50,180 --> 00:49:51,540
Ouch!

481
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:55,900
I don’t think you can walk now.

482
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,780
Get on my back then.

483
00:50:01,660 --> 00:50:02,620
What?

484
00:50:12,600 --> 00:50:16,260
I can’t believe you’re now strong enough to carry me.

485
00:50:19,000 --> 00:50:23,900
Yeah. Back then, I could only stand there and watch Wasu giving you a piggyback ride.

486
00:50:50,700 --> 00:50:54,330
But with your foot hurt like this, will you be able to go on our honeymoon?

487
00:50:54,780 --> 00:50:57,130
Hm? What honeymoon?

488
00:50:58,400 --> 00:51:01,820
Lom suggested that we should go on a honeymoon.

489
00:51:01,820 --> 00:51:04,820
To make our marriage look even more believable.

490
00:51:06,700 --> 00:51:08,700
So, where will we go?

491
00:51:12,330 --> 00:51:13,660
Come on, please tell me a bit.

492
00:51:14,330 --> 00:51:16,700
Nope. I’ll make it a surprise for you.

493
00:51:17,130 --> 00:51:17,930
Please, Din.

494
00:51:19,060 --> 00:51:22,260
1 2 3. So cute.

495
00:51:22,700 --> 00:51:23,660
1 2 3.

496
00:51:25,130 --> 00:51:25,930
Thank you.

497
00:51:28,860 --> 00:51:29,660
Sis.

498
00:51:30,530 --> 00:51:31,140
Hey.

499
00:51:31,140 --> 00:51:31,980
Hi, Rose.

500
00:51:33,700 --> 00:51:34,900
Here’s your keys.

501
00:51:35,760 --> 00:51:36,560
Thanks.

502
00:51:37,100 --> 00:51:40,140
You must be exhausted after a long drive. Please rest well.

503
00:51:41,400 --> 00:51:42,940
Thank you so much, Nam.

504
00:51:43,500 --> 00:51:45,980
Your resort is absolutely stunning.

505
00:51:46,300 --> 00:51:47,140
Thank you.

506
00:51:47,420 --> 00:51:49,780
If you need anything, you can always tell our staff, Sis.

507
00:51:51,260 --> 00:51:53,260
Go on and get back to work. Don’t worry about us.

508
00:51:56,530 --> 00:52:00,200
Okay. I’ll get back to work then.

509
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:05,530
Hope you and Rose will have a pleasant time here.

510
00:52:12,700 --> 00:52:15,860
She seems busy all the time, Din.

511
00:52:16,730 --> 00:52:18,560
Well, she’s a hotel heiress.

512
00:52:18,900 --> 00:52:22,460
Lom often tells me that Nam will probably end up marrying her work.

513
00:52:24,260 --> 00:52:26,020
But I think she’s amazing.

514
00:52:26,020 --> 00:52:30,020
She arranged everything for our wedding and made it incredibly wonderful.

515
00:52:30,340 --> 00:52:33,660
That’s because she’s the genius in our family.

516
00:52:33,660 --> 00:52:36,860
If she has her mind set on anything, there’s never a time she fails to succeed.

517
00:52:37,960 --> 00:52:39,100
Cheers!

518
00:52:42,130 --> 00:52:45,560
Din and Rose are here now. I just gave them the room key.

519
00:52:46,500 --> 00:52:50,330
So, about our plan. Has it gone well?

520
00:52:51,000 --> 00:52:55,960
Don’t worry. With that room I’ve arranged for them, they’ll definitely get to share a romantic moment there.

521
00:52:58,900 --> 00:53:00,530
Okay. Bye.

522
00:53:18,730 --> 00:53:20,460
Din! Din!

523
00:53:21,130 --> 00:53:22,400
Come see the bathroom.

524
00:53:28,730 --> 00:53:30,060
What is it, Rose?

525
00:53:30,700 --> 00:53:35,860
There’s no door. And you can see through these curtains. How are we going to shower then?

526
00:53:37,820 --> 00:53:41,660
Maybe Nam misunderstood and wanted us to have a real honeymoon. Look.

527
00:53:51,600 --> 00:53:54,620
I guess we have to take turns to use the bathroom.

528
00:53:54,620 --> 00:53:57,820
You can shower first. I’ll go wait on the veranda.

529
00:53:58,260 --> 00:53:59,060
Okay.

530
00:54:10,300 --> 00:54:12,530
Geez, Nam. What kind of joke is this?

531
00:54:36,130 --> 00:54:38,100
Why are they all like this?

532
00:54:42,130 --> 00:54:42,940
Moddang.

533
00:54:42,940 --> 00:54:43,460
Yes, Miss?

534
00:54:43,460 --> 00:54:46,780
Make sure you pack modest pjs for me. I have to be considerate of her.

535
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:50,700
You’re going on a honeymoon. Why would you bring modest pjs, Miss?

536
00:54:51,100 --> 00:54:53,660
You should be wearing one that’s sexy and revealing like this.

537
00:54:55,130 --> 00:54:55,930
Moddang.

538
00:54:57,000 --> 00:55:01,730
All right. I’ll pack the most modest pjs there is for you, Miss.

539
00:55:09,100 --> 00:55:10,180
Moddang!

540
00:55:23,730 --> 00:55:28,260
They’re gifts from me, Miss. I bought them especially for you.

541
00:55:46,700 --> 00:55:47,500
Rose.

542
00:55:48,000 --> 00:55:48,800
Yes?

543
00:55:50,060 --> 00:55:51,260
Are you okay?

544
00:55:53,400 --> 00:55:55,400
Is the air-con not cold enough?

545
00:55:56,800 --> 00:55:57,600
Oh!

546
00:56:03,600 --> 00:56:07,330
It’s just…Moddang has packed only this kind of pjs for me.

547
00:56:08,400 --> 00:56:10,930
So, I don’t have anything else to wear.

548
00:56:11,460 --> 00:56:13,580
That’s all right.

549
00:56:13,580 --> 00:56:15,900
We’re both girls. I don’t mind at all.

550
00:56:17,560 --> 00:56:21,780
Then, you should hurry and shower. So that you can rest.

551
00:56:21,780 --> 00:56:24,100
You drove all the way here today.

552
00:56:24,560 --> 00:56:26,740
I’ll…go shower then.

553
00:56:26,740 --> 00:56:27,780
Yes,

554
00:56:45,560 --> 00:56:47,580
Last time when I slept in your room,

555
00:56:48,340 --> 00:56:50,900
did I snore or sleeptalk?

556
00:56:53,100 --> 00:56:55,930
Not at all. You slept like a baby.

557
00:57:01,900 --> 00:57:04,500
Then, should we stay up all night again?

558
00:57:04,580 --> 00:57:06,860
We haven’t finished talking last time.

559
00:57:08,300 --> 00:57:09,100
Oh!

560
00:57:10,900 --> 00:57:12,060
Well…I…

561
00:57:12,730 --> 00:57:14,300
I…

562
00:57:14,460 --> 00:57:16,330
I was afraid you might get cold.

563
00:57:16,960 --> 00:57:17,760
I know.

564
00:57:19,060 --> 00:57:21,730
So, do you want to do it again?

565
00:57:24,500 --> 00:57:27,660
Up to you then. I’ll let you decide.

566
00:57:28,530 --> 00:57:29,800
Up to me again.

567
00:57:31,700 --> 00:57:33,160
We’re going to be together for quite some time.

568
00:57:34,100 --> 00:57:39,500
If you always let me decide, you might end up feeling agitated later on.

569
00:57:40,660 --> 00:57:44,860
Your happiness is also my happiness.

570
00:57:47,760 --> 00:57:49,100
Let’s sleep then.

571
00:57:50,260 --> 00:57:51,060
Good night.

572
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:53,460
Good night.

